{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774284916,"nonce":"OFSTVFf7P3mSAIVDsCtUXBalVZ8=","title":"Provide construct for optional input types","message":"Optional input types are specified using a vector—for example, `#(int null)`. This is a bit clunky. Something like `(optional int)` may be cleaner.\n\nEven `int?` may be an option considering it's already used in the [CWL type DSL](https://www.commonwl.org/v1.2/SchemaSalad.html#Domain_Specific_Language_for_types). However `int?` breaks referential transparency and is less schemey. Notice that we don't support `int[]` for arrays and instead go with `(array int)`.","files":null}]}